With her extensive knowledge of Colorado personal injury law and trial experience, Debbie is well-equipped to handle even the most complex cases. She approaches each case with compassion, understanding the impact accidents have on victims and their families. When you choose Debbie Taussig Law, your best interests will be protected throughout the legal process. We will diligently prepare your case, negotiate with insurance companies on your behalf, and, if needed, take your case to trial. Our goal is to achieve a fair and favorable outcome while alleviating the financial burdens that come with accidents. If you have been injured in a car accident and are looking for a car accident attorney, Debbie Taussig Law is here for you. We have the expertise, dedication, and resources to navigate the complexities of your case. Contact us today for a free consultation and let us fight for the justice and compensation you deserve.

Description: Hello—my name is Drew Moody. Welcome to A Table in the Corner of the Cafe. Feel free to pull up a chair. I built this Table in Spring 2011.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Hello—my name is Drew Moody. Welcome to A Table in the Corner of the Cafe. Feel free to pull up a chair. I built this Table in Spring 2011. At the time, I was a barista at Peet’s Coffee and Tea in Evanston, Illinois—a suburb just north of the great city of Chicago. I left the coffee industry after being in the business for almost ten years to pursue other career interests, but my heart was still with my favorite beverage—coffee. My interests were split in two directions—professional editorial work and specialty coffee. The Table was the great compromise. By starting this blog, I was able to keep one foot in the coffee industry and the other in the corporate world. A Table in the Corner of the Cafe is a blog dedicated to specialty coffee and cafe reviews, primarily, but it also features a wealth of information about coffee, my opinions of the goings on in and of the coffee industry, coffee news, and some fun and games along the way. Most importantly, though, A Table in the Corner of the Cafe is all about community. Please feel free to share your ideas with me, tell me about the things you find interesting, write guest articles, and engage with other readers. There’s always room here at the Table, so feel free to pull up a chair.
